Step 1:- Download JDK 8 tar.gz file from official website 

Step 2:- Extract contents using tar command $tar -xzvf filename.tar.gz 

Step 3 :- Move Extracted file to /usr/local/java Directory

 Step 4: - Update Alternatives 


$sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/java" "java" "/usr/local/java/jdk1.8.0_60/bin/java" 

1 $sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/javac" "javac" "/usr/local/java/jdk1.8.0_60/bin/javac" 

1 $sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/javaws" "javaws" "/usr/local/java/jdk1.8.0_60/bin/javaws" 

1 


Step 5 :- Update bashrc file $sudo gedit ~/.bashrc Step 

6 :- Apply code $Source ~/.bashrc Step 


7 :- Check Java version 

$java -version


